1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,378
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,461 --> 00:00:08,550
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:10,635
♪ <i>Fix this, oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,846
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:15,640
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>In the world's mess…</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,226
[Atoy] <i>This is where she met her date.</i>

8
00:00:18,309 --> 00:00:20,145
My God! [gasps]

9
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:21,062
[Atoy] <i>Raki Roman.</i>

10
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:23,398
[Atoy] <i>Even if he hides</i>
<i>in the eye of a needle,</i>

11
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:24,482
<i>I'll find him.</i>

12
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,443
[receptionist] <i>There's no artist here</i>
<i>named Roman.</i>

13
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:28,528
Uh, not Roman! Uh, Raki!

14
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:29,988
I'm looking for Raki Roman.

15
00:00:30,071 --> 00:00:31,114
- [grunts]
- [man 1] <i>Are you a cop?</i>

16
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:33,116
- [tattooist] <i>He's busy. Just leave.</i>
- [grunts and groans]

17
00:00:33,199 --> 00:00:34,159
PREVIOUSLY

18
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:38,371
- [grunting and groaning]
- [weapons swish and` swoosh]

19
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:39,622
[Raki] <i>What do you want from me?!</i>

20
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:42,417
[Atoy] <i>Do you know Mandy?</i>
<i>She hasn't gone home for a month.</i>

21
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:43,585
I don't know anything about that!

22
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:46,588
[grunting and groaning]

23
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:48,840
[Atoy] <i>What do you know about her parents?</i>

24
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:49,841
[Ame] <i>Nothing.</i>

25
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:51,676
[Ame] Because when I met her,

26
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,178
she was six years old
and already mischievous.

27
00:00:53,261 --> 00:00:56,306
But she said she was just a baby
when she was brought to the orphanage.

28
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:59,684
- You'll look for Ibyang's parents?
- Why not?

29
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:02,353
[Dmitri, in English] <i>I'm looking</i>
<i>for my phone. Did I leave it somewhere?</i>

30
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:03,772
[Audrey, in English] <i>Ah! Here it is, Dad.</i>

31
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:04,981
[in English] Oh, okay.

32
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,191
[Audrey, in English] <i>Is this Mr. Mercado?</i>

33
00:01:06,274 --> 00:01:07,859
[in English] Are you the contact
for The Master Cutter?

34
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:10,278
- [electronic blipping]
- [sauve music playing]

35
00:01:12,113 --> 00:01:13,031
[clangs]

36
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:15,700
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

37
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:18,453
[phone vibrating]

38
00:01:18,536 --> 00:01:19,454
Hello?

39
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:22,248
[in English] Hello? Is this Mr. Mercado?

40
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,501
[Audrey, in English] <i>Are you the contact</i>
<i>for The Master Cutter?</i>

41
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:26,169
Where did you get my number?

42
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:28,171
From Dmitri Regalia.

43
00:01:28,671 --> 00:01:30,173
He was your client.

44
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:31,966
[in English] He's my dad.

45
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:33,468
[in English] Ah, okay.

46
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:36,513
He mentioned you to me and so…

47
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:39,682
He agreed that we should not look for…

48
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:41,559
what he doesn't want you to find.

49
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:42,769
[in English] What?

50
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:44,687
[ominous music playing]

51
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,272
[in English] Are you telling me…

52
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:49,400
that he told you not to accommodate me?

53
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:51,694
Why?

54
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:53,488
[chuckles]

55
00:01:53,571 --> 00:01:55,240
You should talk to him first.

56
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:58,368
[in English] Look, Mr. Mercado,
I'm sorry, but…

57
00:01:58,952 --> 00:01:59,911
[in English] I'm an adult.

58
00:01:59,994 --> 00:02:02,372
[in English] I have my own money,
and I can transact business

59
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,748
with anyone I want to.

60
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:06,668
[Audrey] <i>Without my dad having to know.</i>

61
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:09,712
<i>I'm sure he doesn't control you because…</i>

62
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:12,173
your relationship is transactional.

63
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:14,259
[in English] Why can't I have that too?

64
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,803
[in English] I'd like to hire you
for your services.

65
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:18,263
[tense music playing]

66
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:19,764
[Audrey] <i>I'm willing to pay double.</i>

67
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,432
[music continues]

68
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:24,477
I want to meet the Master Cutter.

69
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:27,230
[music fades]

70
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:34,154
[phone ringing]

71
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,321
[phone clicks]

72
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,199
[in English] Hello? Uh, sir.

73
00:02:38,283 --> 00:02:42,537
[Mercado] <i>Atoy, I spoke</i>
<i>with Mr. Regalia's daughter.</i>

74
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:44,414
She wants someone found.

75
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:47,041
I thought her father didn't want that.

76
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:49,794
[in English] She's willing
to pay double our fees.

77
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:54,883
This is just business.
Her father doesn't need to know.

78
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:56,801
[suspicious music playing]

79
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:58,011
Oh, no, sir.

80
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,305
Wait.

81
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:03,057
Negative on that, sir.

82
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:04,976
[music continues]

83
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:06,352
Let's avoid those things

84
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:09,898
because I'm done with family dramas.

85
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:12,942
That's their father-daughter problem.

86
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,485
Okay, sir.

87
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:18,239
I'm working on something here.

88
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:22,243
Perhaps tomorrow or the next day
I can focus on this.

89
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:24,203
I'll update you right away.

90
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:29,792
Do you have any idea
who she wants us to find?

91
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:31,252
What's the name?

92
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:33,463
She didn't say.

93
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:38,009
That's why she wants to meet you first.

94
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:39,219
[music continues]

95
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:40,970
[in English] Her name is Audrey.

96
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,639
[tense music playing]

97
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,224
Audrey…

98
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,142
[music continues]

99
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:48,519
Audrey Regalia.

100
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:51,231
[music swells]

101
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:52,649
Audrey Regalia.

102
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:55,485
[music fades]

103
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:56,986
Okay, sir.

104
00:03:57,070 --> 00:04:00,782
[sauve theme music playing]

105
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:02,700
[motorcycle revving]

106
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:03,660
[sewing machine whirring]

107
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:04,619
[scratches]

108
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:06,621
[snipping]

109
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:10,500
- [music continues]
- [sewing machine whirring]

110
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,126
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots]

111
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:13,878
- [thumps and gunshots]
- [music intensifies]

112
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:16,172
[clicking]

113
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:18,258
[snipping]

114
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,509
[electronic blipping]

115
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:25,431
[music fades]

116
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:31,396
[upbeat rock music playing]

117
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:33,773
Oh? Sis Tonet!

118
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:35,358
[music continues]

119
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,734
Sis Tonet!

120
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:39,237
[Ibyang] Sis Tonet!

121
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,780
[music continues]

122
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:42,115
Sis Tonet!

123
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,992
[music continues]

124
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:45,285
Sis Tonet!

125
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,288
[squeals] Oh, fat horse!

126
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:49,289
[music fades]

127
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:50,957
Baby girl! [titters]

128
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,417
So, it's you!

129
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,751
What do you need?

130
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,962
Didn't you hear me earlier?

131
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:58,172
Ah, there?

132
00:04:58,673 --> 00:04:59,549
There, oh. Oh!

133
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,386
Listen. That band, Munting Sigaw.

134
00:05:03,469 --> 00:05:07,557
- [growling]
- [hard rock music playing]

135
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,017
Munting Sigaw?

136
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,560
Yes.

137
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:12,103
They keep shouting!

138
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:13,604
[Tonet] Huh?

139
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:17,317
- You don't like them?
- It feels like… my earwax is coming out!

140
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:19,485
[Tonet] Give me that.

141
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:22,030
A friend recommended this to me.

142
00:05:22,113 --> 00:05:24,157
They're good. Wakes you up, right?

143
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:26,826
Oh, you!

144
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:29,704
- Tonet! Where were you last night?
- [Tonet] Oh!

145
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,205
You came home very late.

146
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:32,540
Last night?

147
00:05:32,623 --> 00:05:35,752
Oh, just nearby! I was just pondering.

148
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:38,212
Is it still about Emerson?

149
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:39,881
What's your plan?

150
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,259
Do you want me to talk to him?

151
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:45,887
Oh, no, Miss Cita.

152
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:49,766
I won't force myself on him.

153
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:53,811
And if he's ready to talk, I'm just here.

154
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:56,689
- Okay, just tell me.
- [Tonet] Yes.

155
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,901
Thank you. It's clean now.

156
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:03,279
[gentle music playing]

157
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:15,458
[Enzo] <i>Tell him things you used</i>
<i>to do together.</i>

158
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,834
[pensive music playing]

159
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:18,836
That will make him nostalgic.

160
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:22,215
Then he'll remember your bonding moments.

161
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:27,470
You can rebuild connections
without being pushy.

162
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:32,475
[music continues]

163
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:47,824
[music continues]

164
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:53,079
[phone keys clicking]

165
00:06:53,162 --> 00:06:54,747
[music continues]

166
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:56,332
[line rings]

167
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,960
- [phone vibrates]
- [goat bleats]

168
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,253
[phone clicks]

169
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:01,462
[in English] You like it now?

170
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:05,007
[Tonet on the phone] <i>Yes,</i>
<i>it woke me up this morning.</i>

171
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,303
By the way, I called because
I wanted to thank you for last night.

172
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,807
<i>Thank you for staying with me, and…</i>

173
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:18,104
Because I was able to talk
to someone about my problem.

174
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:19,856
[in English] No worries.

175
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:23,234
You know, you should drop by later.
Your drinks are on me.

176
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:25,653
Was that a goat?

177
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:28,239
- Yes, I'm at the farm.
- [goat bleats]

178
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:32,285
In the morning,
goats and ducks are my friends.

179
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:35,621
At night, drinks and the band.

180
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:37,957
That's nice.

181
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:41,169
I'd like to meet your friends
in the morning.

182
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:42,795
Do you want to come here later?

183
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,255
Maybe next time.

184
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:46,591
Let's just meet at the bar tonight.

185
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:47,717
[Enzo, in English] <i>Perfect.</i>

186
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,260
[somber music playing]

187
00:07:49,343 --> 00:07:50,219
Bye.

188
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,346
[music fades]

189
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,183
Hey!

190
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:57,351
Big Brother Atoy,
you're a fan of Raki too?

191
00:07:57,435 --> 00:07:58,728
Didn't expect that!

192
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,146
[ominous music playing]

193
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:02,315
- Do you know him?
- Yes.

194
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:05,026
He's the primary suspect
in Queenie's disappearance.

195
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,069
- [Karla] What?
- And also the other girl, Mandy.

196
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,781
They were both last seen
dating him before they vanished.

197
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:12,700
He's a kidnapper?!

198
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:17,497
Just a suspect. But he looks guilty.

199
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:21,709
Because when I went to him
and talked, he ran away.

200
00:08:21,792 --> 00:08:25,338
But Tonet and I met up
with him the other day.

201
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:26,339
[Cita] What?!

202
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:30,468
My God, Karla! Why are you
befriending people like that?

203
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:33,346
If not street idlers,
kidnappers are your friends!

204
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:34,972
Mom, it's not like that!

205
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:36,766
He has a punk rock band.

206
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,100
The Munting Sigaw.

207
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:40,353
[music fades]

208
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,272
What? Why?

209
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,733
What? Did a fly get into your mouth?

210
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:50,363
Nothing. I just remembered…

211
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:53,950
That's what Sis Tonet
was listening to earlier.

212
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,660
Munting Sigaw!

213
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:58,621
Really? Tonet, a rocker?

214
00:08:58,704 --> 00:08:59,830
[suspicious music playing]

215
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:00,748
Where's Tonet?

216
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:04,627
I told her to deliver
an order at Santa Fe.

217
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:07,630
Then she said she'd go
straight to her appointment.

218
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,298
I'll call her.

219
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:10,800
[Atoy] Call her, call her.

220
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:11,717
[phone keys click]

221
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,052
[line rings]

222
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:18,140
[tense music playing]

223
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:22,019
- [lively chatter]
- Hey, psst! Hey, hey! Psst!

224
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:23,187
It's already late!

225
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:24,939
That's why you smell like
you were under the sun all day!

226
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:27,024
- He doesn't grow taller!
- [man] Huh?

227
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,568
Ugly!

228
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:30,278
Hideous. What? Let me see.

229
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:31,487
See my shot here?

230
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,030
Hold it. Like this, oh.

231
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:35,032
- Oh, okay.
- When I shoot like that, whoops!

232
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:36,367
- Did it go in?
- Not really.

233
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,451
Oh. Too bad.

234
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:39,161
- Almost though.
- [chuckles]

235
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,247
I even did a fadeaway like that.

236
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:42,707
[man] He's skinny!

237
00:09:43,207 --> 00:09:45,793
- No. That's me! I'm on a diet.
- [chuckles]

238
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:47,420
I told you.

239
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:48,713
- [lively chatter]
- [hushes]

240
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:51,591
[Emerson] Hey. Who put this here?

241
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:54,427
Oh. We don't know, brother. What's inside?

242
00:09:58,139 --> 00:10:04,186
[gentle music playing]

243
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,650
[Tonet] <i>Big Brother, I miss you,</i>

244
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:12,820
<i>and I love you, no matter what happens.</i>

245
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:16,490
<i>I'm here whenever you want to talk to me.</i>

246
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:19,660
<i>This is for you. Roast pig.</i>

247
00:10:19,744 --> 00:10:21,787
<i>You can have it now.</i>

248
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:24,999
<i>You deserve it because you're successful.</i>

249
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:25,916
<i>Netchai.</i>

250
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:26,834
[music fades]

251
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,252
[in Visayan] Big Brother,

252
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:32,465
when will we get to eat
real roast pig again?

253
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:35,509
[in Visayan] We're always just pretending.

254
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:38,638
[in Visayan] Do you want me to buy this?

255
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:41,599
[in Visayan] So it can finally be real.

256
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:43,351
[in Visayan] Don't bother.
Let's just be patient a little longer.

257
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:46,937
Your money might not be enough.
We will still need it for the water

258
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,689
and electricity bill.

259
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:55,446
[in Visayan] Once I saved enough
and become successful,

260
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:57,948
we'll eat this every day.
Real roast pig, not imaginary!

261
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:01,327
[in Visayan] We might get high
blood pressure if we eat it every day!

262
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:03,871
[in Visayan] Once a week is enough!

263
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:05,206
[laughs]

264
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:08,918
[gentle music playing]

265
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:11,212
[pleasant music playing]

266
00:11:11,295 --> 00:11:13,881
It is food! [chuckles]

267
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:20,054
[gentle music playing]

268
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,475
[T-bak] It is roast pig.

269
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:26,310
[music fades]

270
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:31,065
[sneaky music playing]

271
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:32,024
Oh.

272
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,567
[music continues]

273
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,736
Oh, Big Brother…. Big Brother!

274
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,155
Big Brother… Brother Emerson!

275
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:40,116
Big Brother, are you throwing it away?

276
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:41,575
[titters]

277
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:43,911
That's Cebu roast pig!
Give it to me instead!

278
00:11:43,994 --> 00:11:46,747
Hmm, what do you mean just you?
We'll share it!

279
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:49,542
- [titters]
- [T-bak] Oh, Big Brother…

280
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:51,001
Okay, Big Brother, let go.

281
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:53,337
- [titters]
- Big Brother, let it go already.

282
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,255
[grunts]

283
00:11:54,338 --> 00:11:56,257
I told you, let it go.

284
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,592
I told you it's roast pig!

285
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,719
Thank you, Big Brother! Hmm!

286
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:03,722
[music fades]

287
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,641
- [T-bak] Big Brother.
- You don't need this.

288
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,811
- Huh?
- What you need is a diet.

289
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:09,728
Huh?

290
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,647
[pleasant music playing]

291
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,815
What's this!

292
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:16,235
It's roast pig. Now it's invisible!

293
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:18,112
It's your fault. You're too slow!

294
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:19,947
Is it my fault I'm slow?!

295
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,157
Yes!

296
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:27,037
- [rock music playing]
- [bustling chattering]

297
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:36,547
[Enzo] Tonet! Tonet!

298
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,090
- Ah!
- [in English] Thank you for coming.

299
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,801
- Ma'am, your order.
- [woman] Thank you.

300
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:42,553
Um, sorry, I didn't mention earlier.

301
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:45,014
There's an event here tonight,
punk rock bands.

302
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:47,141
More people will come,
and it'll get louder!

303
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:50,227
Huh?! Louder and more people?!

304
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:51,187
More people are coming.

305
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,813
[Tonet] But there are
so many people here already.

306
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:55,691
Um, if you want,
we can go to another place.

307
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,693
Uh, what about your shift?

308
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:58,986
I'll ask someone to cover for me.

309
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:01,030
What's important is we talk properly.

310
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,824
No! I'm fine here! This is okay! Yes.

311
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,201
- Are your sure?
- Yes.

312
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:07,453
- [line beeping]
- She's not answering.

313
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:10,998
Ibyang, did she say which friend
she's meeting up with?

314
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,416
Was it Raki?

315
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,543
[suspicious music playing]

316
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,128
[Ibyang] She didn't say.

317
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:21,258
But she said a friend recommended it.

318
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,344
It wasn't the friend in the band.

319
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:28,390
You know, I have a feeling
it's someone else, not Raki.

320
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:30,226
Tonet is marked safe.

321
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:32,019
[music continues]

322
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:34,021
Where is this band playing?

323
00:13:34,104 --> 00:13:36,023
They have a fan page. I'll check.

324
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:37,983
[phone keys clicking]

325
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,568
Here, they have a gig!

326
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,654
Punk Man event at On The Edge music bar.

327
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:43,155
It's tonight!

328
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:44,323
[rock music playing]

329
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,116
Okay, here's the plan.
I'll prepare your drink.

330
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,701
Then I'll ask for an event pass.

331
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:49,370
- [Tonet] Huh?
- In case they kick you out.

332
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:50,621
- Oh! Okay!
- [Enzo] Huh?

333
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,039
- Okay!
- [in English] Thank you!

334
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:57,419
[music continues]

335
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:01,590
[Raki, in English] Tonet, you're here!

336
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:03,259
[in English] You came for our band?

337
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:08,013
Me? No! I'm with Enzo!

338
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:10,891
Come with me instead. Let's go!

339
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,434
No, I'm fine here.

340
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,562
No, come on. Come with me.

341
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:16,146
- [music continues]
- [grunts]

342
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,440
Is that really how you approach women?

343
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:20,109
You're a red flag!

344
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:22,653
Just because you're a rockstar
doesn't mean you can get everything!

345
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:25,155
Don't you get it? I don't like you!

346
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:28,033
That's what I like.
Those who play hard to get.

347
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:29,535
Come on!

348
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:31,745
- [music fades]
- [bustling chattering]

349
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:33,289
[Enzo] Raki!

350
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:34,790
[rock music playing]

351
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:35,958
Leave Tonet alone!

352
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,585
[music continues]

353
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:39,587
[in English] Okay, fine.

354
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:45,301
- [music continues]
- [bustling chattering]

355
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:49,680
Are you okay?

356
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:55,895
- [bustling chattering]
- [suspicious music playing]

357
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,816
Big Brother, Raki and Tonet are together.

358
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,402
There's a picture uploaded
on Munting Sigaw's fan page.

359
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:06,989
[mysterious music playing]

360
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:11,035
Atoy, what if Raki is really
the "friend" Tonet mentioned?

361
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:15,623
Tonet even fits the description
of the missing girls he dated.

362
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:18,208
No family.

363
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,794
[in English] Neglected,
with family problems.

364
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,212
Exactly.

365
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:24,048
All right, all right.

366
00:15:24,131 --> 00:15:30,387
Uh… Netchai? Or Tonet,
or whatever name she uses.

367
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:33,641
Return this to her.
Tell her she can't bribe me.

368
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,226
She shouldn't leave things
like this at my door.

369
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:39,021
That's the reason Tonet
is getting close to kidnappers,

370
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,522
because you keep pushing her away!

371
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,441
What kidnapper?

372
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:43,817
Well, it's not confirmed yet.

373
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:45,736
But he's with Tonet right now.

374
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:49,448
[suspicious music playing]

375
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:50,991
That's your fault.

376
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:53,577
Your responsibility. You let her go.

377
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,120
Stop it!

378
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,831
Just leave if you don't care
about your sister!

379
00:15:58,832 --> 00:16:00,125
Atoy, go on. Be careful.

380
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:01,752
- Yes, yes.
- Bring Tonet home right away.

381
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:06,507
[music swells]

382
00:16:07,508 --> 00:16:09,259
[music fades]

383
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:13,263
[sauve music playing]

384
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:14,264
[car door clicks open]

385
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:17,518
[music continues]

386
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:19,937
- [car doors close]
- [music fades]

387
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:21,897
What are you doing?

388
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:27,027
Uh, I just want to see
how you'll bring Tonet home.

389
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:28,570
[scoffs]

390
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:29,989
You talk too much!

391
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:31,448
Put your seatbelt on. Let's go!

392
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:32,700
[rock music playing]

393
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,368
[car engine starts]

394
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:39,206
[tires screech]

395
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:41,458
[music fades]

396
00:16:41,542 --> 00:16:45,295
[rock music playing]

397
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:49,758
Uh, this is a convention
of… sleepless and scruffy people.

398
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:52,052
Stitch your mouth shut.
Someone might hear you.

399
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:55,764
[music continues]

400
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:57,099
[in English] Oops, oops, ticket!

401
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:58,726
[music continues]

402
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:00,352
Uh…

403
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,187
Boss, where do we buy tickets?

404
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,023
Step aside. This isn't a ticket office.

405
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:06,692
- Uh, no. Oh, Uh…
- Boss, tickets are sold out.

406
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:08,110
[guest 1] Sorry for you.

407
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:10,279
No, b-boss, my sister is with a criminal.

408
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,239
I just want to check if she's inside.

409
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:14,366
You're both making excuses! Leave!

410
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,284
[guest 2] Line up at the back!

411
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:18,454
- Yes! Line up at the back!
- Oh, fine, fine, fine! Let's go, let's go!

412
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,663
How do we get in?

413
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,123
Why don't you just fight your way in?

414
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:23,751
Look at all these people.
What, you want us mobbed?

415
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:26,336
You're so weak.

416
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:29,548
[rock music playing]

417
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:30,632
We'll get in.

418
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,926
[music continues]

419
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:34,011
[Emerson] Where?

420
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,596
[music fades]

421
00:17:35,679 --> 00:17:38,223
- Boss.
- Oh, sir! Buy here, sir!

422
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:39,975
- Sir.
- We've got plenty here, sir.

423
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,268
[Atoy] That's it.

424
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:44,730
Nice. Nice stuff you're selling.

425
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:51,278
Bro, we just need your help because…

426
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:55,574
we lost our tickets.

427
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,659
- Yes, yes.
- We want to get inside On The Edge bar.

428
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,745
- We lost our tickets.
- Oh!

429
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,997
Yes, yes. We're fans of…

430
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,416
- of Munting Sigaw.
- Munting Sigaw, yes!

431
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,793
- Munting Sigaw?
- We're fans too!

432
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:07,086
[Atoy] Oh! You are too!

433
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:08,837
- [chuckles]
- Awesome! Right?

434
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:10,214
Imagine that!

435
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:13,092
Bro, maybe you can let us join you,

436
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,510
get us inside!

437
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:16,011
We'll buy whatever you're selling.

438
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:19,348
If it's just the two of you,
and you'll buy a lot,

439
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:20,682
tickets are free.

440
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,601
Huh? Really?

441
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:25,062
[in English] Nice one!

442
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:26,855
You're great, bro!

443
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,273
- [chuckles]
- Is that good, Uncle?

444
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,942
- [titters]
- [chuckles] Uh…

445
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:31,401
[sarcastic chuckle]

446
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:34,404
If only we weren't fans of Munting Sigaw…

447
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:35,948
Yes, exactly.

448
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:39,118
[both] Munting Sigaw? Whispered scream!

449
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,410
[Emerson] Mmm, whispered scream!

450
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:42,162
- Whispered scream! Yes! Munting Sigaw!
- Oh!

451
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:43,580
[both] Whispered scream!

452
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:49,586
[rock music playing]

453
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,678
[both, in English] Rock on!

454
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:04,309
[rock music playing]

455
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:06,770
[crowd cheering]

456
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:11,233
♪ <i>Don't make it harder anymore</i> ♪

457
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:17,072
♪ <i>You don't need to worry…</i> ♪

458
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:22,327
[hard rock music playing]

459
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:29,835
[Emerson] Netchai?

460
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:31,712
Netchai!

461
00:19:31,795 --> 00:19:37,009
[music continues]

462
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:38,051
[Emerson] Netchai!

463
00:19:38,135 --> 00:19:43,765
[song continues]

464
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:44,892
Netchai!

465
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:51,815
[song continues]

466
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:55,402
Netchai!

467
00:19:55,485 --> 00:20:00,490
[song continues]

468
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:02,993
- Let's split up! Find…
- Huh?!

469
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:04,953
Let's split up! You find Tonet!

470
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,455
I'll look for Raki!

471
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,040
Okay, okay! Okay!

472
00:20:08,123 --> 00:20:11,210
- [crowd cheering]
- [song continues]

473
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:12,544
[Emerson] Netchai!

474
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,379
Oh, oh… Big Sis.

475
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:15,923
- [crowd cheering]
- [song continues]

476
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:17,633
Big Sis…

477
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:20,552
- [crowd cheering]
- [song continues]

478
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:21,595
Big Sis. [clears throat]

479
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:24,056
- [crowd cheering]
- [song continues]

480
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:28,310
Do your parents know…
that you look like that here,

481
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:30,729
and you're with someone
whose hair looks like that?

482
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:33,148
What?! My parents aren't here!

483
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,651
- Huh?!
- My parents aren't here!

484
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:37,611
Oh, you don't realize…

485
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:40,489
What I'm saying is, maybe…
he's a kidnapper!

486
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:41,615
Do you have a sibling?

487
00:20:41,698 --> 00:20:43,116
I have a brother!

488
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,744
He knows I'm here and dressed like this!

489
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:49,998
- What?!
- He knows I'm here and dressed like this!

490
00:20:50,707 --> 00:20:53,210
He wouldn't allow you to look like that!

491
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:56,338
He's here! That's my brother!

492
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:58,423
- Him?
- [woman] Yes!

493
00:20:58,507 --> 00:21:02,386
We share the same music interest,
so we support each other!

494
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:06,556
And he's watching over me,
so no kidnappers can get close to me!

495
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:12,145
[song continues,
melancholic background music]

496
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:18,235
Sir, are you okay?

497
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:20,404
- Huh?
- Are you okay, sir?

498
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:22,030
[song continues,
melancholic background music]

499
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,949
Mm-mm, yes.

500
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:25,575
Well, uh…

501
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:28,370
I'm looking for my… my sister.

502
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:30,122
That's why I'm here!

503
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:32,541
Uh, her name is Netchai.

504
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:35,669
Here, look. Maybe you know her.

505
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:36,962
That's her picture.

506
00:21:37,838 --> 00:21:39,965
It's my fault she's here.

507
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:42,134
I was too stubborn.

508
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:47,973
- [crowd cheering]
- [rock music playing]

509
00:21:49,182 --> 00:21:55,522
- [crowd cheering, growling]
- [rock music playing]

510
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:08,869
Sir.

511
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:10,662
[song continues]

512
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:13,040
Uh, sir, wait. I'm just
looking for something.

513
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:16,043
[song continues]

514
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:17,252
Sir…

515
00:22:18,462 --> 00:22:21,757
Raki's band, Munting Sigaw.

516
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,342
Do you know if they're here?

517
00:22:23,425 --> 00:22:26,219
Uh, yes, sir. They're in the green room.

518
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:28,847
After this band,
they'll be the ones to perform.

519
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,058
Where's the green room?

520
00:22:31,641 --> 00:22:33,101
Just at the back, near the office.

521
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:38,398
- [crowd cheering]
- [tense music playing]

522
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:42,235
- Is this what you're looking for?
- Oh. Thank you, sir. Thank you.

523
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:43,570
Okay.

524
00:22:43,653 --> 00:22:45,781
- [crowd cheering]
- [music continues]

525
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,115
[Atoy] Aries.

526
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:48,492
Ah, yes. I'm Aries.

527
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:54,873
- [crowd cheering]
- [music swells]

528
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:58,251
[groans]

529
00:22:58,335 --> 00:22:59,211
[Enzo] Tonet?

530
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:02,506
Tonet, are you okay? Huh?

531
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:04,424
I'm feeling a bit dizzy.

532
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:05,801
I told you.

533
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:07,677
It's too noisy here.

534
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:09,638
Better if we step outside,
so you can get some air.

535
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:11,932
I'd rather just go home.

536
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:14,518
Okay. I'll take you.

537
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:17,479
But let's go through the back exit.
The front is too crowded.

538
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:18,438
Huh? Let's go.

539
00:23:18,522 --> 00:23:21,399
[rousing music playing]

540
00:23:21,483 --> 00:23:22,317
[door clicks open]

541
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,819
[bustling chattering]

542
00:23:23,902 --> 00:23:26,947
[rock music playing]

543
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,031
Where's Raki?

544
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:30,575
[music continues]

545
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:31,660
Hey.

546
00:23:31,743 --> 00:23:32,828
[music continues]

547
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:34,830
Hey, wait. No entry here
unless you're part of the staff.

548
00:23:34,913 --> 00:23:38,125
[music continues]

549
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,585
Raki, how are you?

550
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:42,879
Wait. Who are you?!

551
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,172
[tense music playing]

552
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,715
Don't you recognize me?

553
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:48,260
[music continues]

554
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:49,803
I'm from the tattoo shop.

555
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:52,430
You ran away from me.

556
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,933
So? We still need to talk.

557
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:56,560
[music swells]

558
00:23:56,643 --> 00:24:00,063
Come on. Let's talk outside.

559
00:24:00,147 --> 00:24:01,606
Okay, let's talk outside.

560
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,859
I've got nothing to hide from you.

561
00:24:04,651 --> 00:24:05,610
Let's go.

562
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:11,366
[music swells]

563
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:23,253
- [electronic blipping]
- [intense music playing]

564
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:26,464
[Raki] Rock and roll!

565
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,133
- [crowd cheering]
- [sauve theme music playing]

566
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:29,968
‪UP NEXT

567
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:31,845
Rock and roll!

568
00:24:31,928 --> 00:24:35,223
- [crowd cheering]
- [music continues]

569
00:24:36,183 --> 00:24:37,017
[Enzo, in English] Welcome home.

570
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:40,187
Later, I'll introduce you
to one of my friends.

571
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,980
You're not kind.

572
00:24:42,063 --> 00:24:44,900
Liar! Loser! Demon!

573
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:46,151
What?!

574
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,569
- [wails]
- What did you say?!

575
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:49,654
[Raki] That's Enzo. He was here earlier.

576
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,615
[Raki] <i>She's dating him, not me.</i>

577
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:54,034
He's the kidnapper.

578
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:55,577
Tonet!

579
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:57,120
[Enzo] Tonet, where are you?!

580
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:58,747
[music continues]

581
00:24:58,830 --> 00:25:00,540
These tire marks are from Enzo's car.

582
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:04,336
Is there a nearby farm or goat pen?

583
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:05,587
There is.

584
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:07,172
[music swells]

585
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:09,007
♪ <i>Like a bubble! Like a bubble!</i> ♪

586
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:11,051
♪ <i>When the cutter strikes</i>
<i>It knows where to land</i> ♪

587
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:13,178
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

588
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:14,179
Subtitle translation by:
Geraldine M. Andong
